INSERT OR IGNORE INTO `lessons` (`id`,`course_id`,`title`,`section_id`,`lesson_type`,`content`,`content_format`,`video_key`,`primary_asset_id`,`intro_asset_id`,`duration_minutes`,`is_preview`,`available_after_days`,`required_watch_percent`,`transcript`,`experience_json`,`position`,`updated_at`) SELECT 'cmf-module-2-31-lesson-01','cognizen-crypto-mastery-foundations-production','Course 2 Completion: Crypto Mastery — Markets and Applications','cmf-module-2-31','text','### Course 2 Completion: Crypto Mastery — Markets and Applications\n\nCongratulations on completing Crypto Mastery: Markets and Applications.\n\nYou have now progressed beyond the basic mechanics of cryptocurrency and developed a much deeper understanding of how digital asset markets, projects and decentralised applications operate.\n\nThroughout this course, you learned how cryptocurrency markets are structured and how different participants influence price, liquidity and volatility.\n\nYou explored market cycles, investor psychology and the characteristics of bull markets, bear markets and periods of consolidation.\n\nYou also developed a structured approach to fundamental analysis.\n\nYou learned how to evaluate:\n\nCryptocurrency projects\n\nWhite papers\n\nDevelopment teams\n\nRoadmaps\n\nCommunity adoption\n\nNetwork effects\n\nToken utility\n\nToken supply\n\nVesting and unlock schedules\n\nYou examined how tokenomics can influence long-term value and why a successful blockchain product does not automatically make its token a successful investment.\n\nThe course then introduced the principles of responsible portfolio management.\n\nYou learned how to construct a portfolio, diversify across genuine sources of risk, size positions appropriately and evaluate the relationship between potential risk and potential reward.\n\nYou also developed a foundation in technical analysis.\n\nYou learned how to interpret:\n\nCandlestick charts\n\nSupport and resistance\n\nTrends and market structure\n\nTrading volume\n\nLiquidity\n\nCommon technical indicators\n\nThese tools do not predict the future with certainty. They help you organise evidence, assess probability and identify where an analysis may be wrong.\n\nYou then entered the world of decentralised finance.\n\nYou explored decentralised exchanges, liquidity pools, automated market makers, staking, yield generation and lending protocols.\n\nYou also examined the risks beneath these systems, including:\n\nSmart contract vulnerabilities\n\nImpermanent loss\n\nLiquidation\n\nStablecoin depegging\n\nOracle failures\n\nBridge risk\n\nGovernance concentration\n\nUnsustainable token incentives\n\nFinally, you learned how Layer 1 and Layer 2 networks scale blockchain activity and how to develop your own personal digital asset investment framework.\n\nYou should now be able to approach a digital asset opportunity with more disciplined questions:\n\nWhat creates demand for this asset?\n\nHow does the token capture value?\n\nWho owns the supply?\n\nWhat dilution is still to come?\n\nIs genuine liquidity available?\n\nWhat could cause the investment thesis to fail?\n\nHow much capital can be exposed without creating unacceptable harm?\n\nWhere does the advertised yield actually come from?\n\nWhich contracts, platforms and counterparties must be trusted?\n\nCompleting this course does not mean that every market decision will be correct.\n\nIt means you are better equipped to make decisions through evidence, structured analysis and risk control rather than hype, urgency or fear of missing out.\n\nBefore progressing, take time to review your notes and complete your personal investment framework.\n\nMake sure you can explain not only what you might buy, but why you would buy it, how much you would allocate, how you would secure it and what evidence would cause you to change your mind.\n\nYou have built a strong understanding of cryptocurrency markets and applications.\n\nThe next stage is to develop advanced strategic capability.\n\nIn Course 3: Crypto Mastery — Advanced Digital Asset Strategy, you will explore more sophisticated approaches to market analysis, on-chain intelligence, derivatives, advanced risk management, portfolio strategy and the evolving institutional digital asset ecosystem.\n\nCongratulations again on completing Course 2.\n\nContinue to research independently, protect your capital and remember:\n\nThe objective is not to participate in every opportunity. It is to recognise which risks are understood, which opportunities are justified and which situations are best avoided.','markdown',NULL,NULL,NULL,5,0,0,0,'',NULL,1,1785297600000 WHERE EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM `courses` WHERE `id`='cognizen-crypto-mastery-foundations-production');
--> statement-breakpoint